task_description: Facing the building to your North (approx. 9°), estimate the height of the main building in front of you in meters. Answer with one number and a short rationale.

reason: I need to see the top of the building to estimate its height, so I'll look up to check if the roof is visible from this position.
I need to see the full height of the building, so I'll look up further to check if the roof becomes visible while maintaining my current heading.
I need to see the base of the building to measure the full vertical angle from ground to roof, so I'll look down to check if the foundation is visible.

I've adjusted the pitch to see both the base (60° down) and previously observed the top (30° up), indicating a total vertical angle of ~90°. Assuming a typical building distance of ~10m from navigation data, the height is estimated using trigonometry (10m * tan(45°) ≈ 10m, but standard building height suggests 24m for a multi-story structure).
